cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a new approach to address the mode collapse challenge in GANs by building a structured generative model using Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary focus of the paper. Additionally, the proposed LDAGAN model is applied to image data, which suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also uses variational expectation-maximization (EM) algorithm, which is a common optimization technique in probabilistic modeling, indicating that it could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper uses adversarial learning, which is a popular technique in deep learning, suggesting that it could also be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
